>Clemens,
>
>I think that Dave's point was that I and others have sloppily =

>used the term "RMS power" when we should have written "average power".
>
>"RMS" is better applied to amplitudes, whose average is zero, =

>yet for which we desire some measure of the "average" =

>significance of that amplitude.
>
>Here is a ham link on this theme:
>http://www.eznec.com/Amateur/RMS_Power.pdf
>
>--Kirk
>
>
