>>Ok, you mean average power. There's no such thing as RMS power.
>
>>That is Prms exists in the mathematical sense, but nobody uses it.
>
>?????????
>As soon you have to deal with measurement of noise,SNR,or =

>unlinear signals, RMS power is essential as is RMS voltage.
>There were application notes from HP how to calculate RMS =

>power from the PEP measurments of their old spectrum analyzers =

>like the HP141 system.
>Today that is all done in software.
>The S-meter of my Perseus SDR can be toggled between reading =

>in RMS of peak power.
