>>Dave,
>>
>>Actually, the formula I gave differs from by a factor of 2 =

>from the one =

>>I usually use, because I use rms power rather than peak power.
>>
>>So, I'm happy to use the version 3 lambda^2 / 8 pi, which =

>appears, for =

>>example, in eq. 18 of my note =

>>http://puhep1.princeton.edu/~mcdonald/examples/power.pdf
>>
>>You are correct that besides power absorbed by the matched load =

>>(neglecting losses), power is scattered out of the incident =

>wave (into =

>>the radiation
>>pattern of the antenna).   Typically, the scattered power equals the
>>absorbed power, as you noted.
>>
>>--Kirk
